# Bootstrap Best Practices

This document outlines essential guidelines for writing maintainable and modern Bootstrap code. By following these practices, you will ensure that your code is efficient, clean, and ready for the future.

## Code Organization and Structure

### Use the Grid System for Layouts
Always utilize Bootstrap's grid system to manage layouts. This approach eliminates the need for manual media queries.

❌ BAD:  
```html
<div style="width: 100%; max-width: 1200px; margin: auto;">
  <div style="float: left; width: 50%;">Left</div>
  <div style="float: right; width: 50%;">Right</div>
</div>
```

✅ GOOD:  
```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-6">Left</div>
    <div class="col-6">Right</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Mobile-First Approach
Define base styles for the smallest screens first, then override with breakpoint-specific classes. This ensures optimal performance on mobile devices.

✅ GOOD:  
```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-12 col-md-6">Left</div>
    <div class="col-12 col-md-6">Right</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Common Patterns and Anti-patterns

### Favor Utility Classes
Use Bootstrap's built-in utility classes for spacing and alignment instead of custom CSS. This keeps your HTML clean and your styles consistent.

❌ BAD:  
```html
<div class="content" style="margin: 20px; padding: 10px;">
  Content here
</div>
```

✅ GOOD:  
```html
<div class="content m-3 p-2">
  Content here
</div>
```

## Performance Considerations

### Load Only Required Components
Always load only the components you need to minimize your bundle size. This practice enhances page load times and performance.

✅ GOOD:  
```scss
@import "~bootstrap/scss/functions";
@import "~bootstrap/scss/variables";
@import "~bootstrap/scss/grid"; // Only import grid system
```

## Common Pitfalls and Gotchas

### Avoid Overriding Default Styles
Instead of overriding Bootstrap's default styles, customize your theme using Sass variables or CSS custom properties. This approach maintains consistency and reduces maintenance.

❌ BAD:  
```css
.btn {
  background-color: red !important; /* Avoid this */
}
```

✅ GOOD:  
```scss
$primary: red; // Change primary color
@import "~bootstrap/scss/bootstrap"; // Re-import Bootstrap
```

## Component Architecture

### Create Reusable Components
When advanced styling is required, create reusable components rather than applying global CSS overrides. This promotes modularity and reusability.

✅ GOOD:  
```html
<div class="card my-custom-card">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h5 class="card-title">Card Title</h5>
    <p class="card-text">Some quick example text.</p>
  </div>
</div>
```

## State Management

### Use Data Attributes for State
Leverage Bootstrap's data attributes (e.g., `data-bs-theme`) for managing state without additional JavaScript. This keeps your code clean and efficient.

✅ GOOD:  
```html
<button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" data-bs-theme="dark">Toggle Theme</button>
```

## Accessibility

### Ensure Focus Management
Always ensure that focus is managed correctly, especially for interactive components. Use ARIA roles and properties where necessary to enhance accessibility.

✅ GOOD:  
```html
<button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" aria-label="Close" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
```

## Theming

### Utilize Sass Variables for Theming
Use Bootstrap's Sass variables to create a consistent theme across your application. This allows for easy updates and maintenance.

✅ GOOD:  
```scss
$body-bg: #f8f9fa; // Set body background
$primary: #007bff; // Set primary color
@import "~bootstrap/scss/bootstrap"; // Import Bootstrap
```

## Conclusion

By adhering to these best practices, you will create maintainable, efficient, and modern Bootstrap code. Always remember to test your layouts on real devices to ensure functionality and usability. Happy coding!